#  Docker Commands
1. docker images -> returns the list of all the images on the system.
2. docker ps -> returns the list of all the running containers on the system.
3. docker pull <image-name>: <tag-version> -> fetches the image
4. docker run <image-name>: <tag-version> -> runs the image
5. docker run -d <image-name>: <tag-version> -> runs the image in detached mode
6. docker logs <container-id>: 
7. dokcer stop <container-id>: 
8. docker run -d -p <host-port>: <conatiner-port> <image-name>: <tag-version>: exposes the container by binding it to port.




# What is Docker 

Virtualization tool.
Makes the development and deployment process easier.
Packages the code along with the config, dependencies, system tools and run time. -> Standardised unit to run an application.




